      "name": "Missing Science Keywords",
      "what": "Tends to describe what happens using everyday words but occasionally leaves out the specific scientific terms the markers need to see.",
      "specific_examples": [
        {
          "questionRef": "[2]",
          "type": "oeq",
          "whatWentWrong": "Kaiyangnggg understood the soup would take longer to boil, but missed the keyword that there is 'more mass' to heat up."
        },
        {
          "questionRef": "[15]",
          "type": "oeq",
          "whatWentWrong": "He knew the chocolate expanded and burst, but forgot to state that it 'gained heat' and expanded 'more than' the bun."
        },
        {
          "questionRef": "[37]",
          "type": "oeq",
          "whatWentWrong": "Kaiyangnggg correctly noted the layers of air, but missed the magic phrase that 'air is a poor conductor of heat'."
        }
      ],
      "strategic_advice": "When you see **'explain why'** or **'give a reason'**, think about the invisible science happening.\n- Always include the energy transfer (e.g., **'gained heat'** or **'lost heat'**).\n- Mention specific properties (e.g., **'poor conductor of heat'** or **'more mass'**).",
      "trigger_keywords": [
        "Explain why",
